<center><h1> Situation Metaphor (Contd) </h1>

<h2><u> Development Schema </u> </h2></center>


<h2> The deveopment Schema consists of three phases </h2>
<h2>

<ol>
<li>Design</li>
<li>Framework </li>
<li>Tools Development</li>
</ol>


1.<u> Design </u>
 
         This stage describes the theoritical devlopment of the situation
         metaphor.It involves situated interaction, situation space and
         functional features etc.



2.<u>Framework</u>

         This stage acts as the middleware to centralise the processing
         and management of the user'situational information.It is a basis
         to include the situated intearction in the prototype application
         tools.



3.<u>Tools devlopment </u>

         The tools would be able to utilize the fuctional features and
         described in framework to provide more situated interaction.




<center>Development Schema </center>
